## What this project is

A Manifest V3 browser extension (Firefox + Chromium) that:

1. Stores CUNY login credentials (email, password, TOTP secret) encrypted in `browser.storage.local` using PBKDF2 + AES-GCM.
2. Keeps the vault unlocked across popup opens for the lifetime of the browser session using `browser.storage.session`.
3. Injects a content script on `https://ssologin.cuny.edu/*` that auto-fills the Oracle SSO login and TOTP pages when the vault session is valid, and also responds to manual `FILL_CREDENTIALS` messages from the popup.

Master-password handling, `storage.local` vs `storage.session`, and related security rules are defined only in the **Security, crypto, and gotchas** project ruleâ€”do not contradict that rule.

Saved email must end with **`@login.cuny.edu`** (enforced in `popup.ts`).

The extension display name in `src/manifest.json` is **CUNYAutoLogin**.

## Project layout

```
popup.html                      Vite entry point for the popup UI (no static dev controls; see debug panel below)
src/
  popup/popup.ts                Modes setup / locked / unlocked; encrypt/save; session unlock; master rotation;
                                draft autosave; dynamic-import debug panel when MODE=development
  popup/debugPanel.ts           Debug-only: test FILL_CREDENTIALS + clear vault (not bundled in production build)
  popup/popup.css               Popup styles
  crypto/vault.ts               PBKDF2 + AES-GCM encrypt/decrypt; `VAULT_STORAGE_KEY`, payload types
  content/content.ts            IIFE bundle: MutationObserver waits for JET inputs; fill login + TOTP;
                                `AUTO_FILL_REQUEST` + `FILL_CREDENTIALS` handling
  background/service-worker.ts  onInstalled log; `AUTO_FILL_REQUEST` â†’ decrypt vault via session master
  manifest.json                 Source manifest (copied to dist/ by Vite)
vite.config.ts                  Builds popup + background as ES modules; copies manifest
vite.content.config.ts          Builds `content.ts` as a single IIFE (`dist/content.js`, inline deps)
dist/                           Built extension â€” load this folder in the browser
```

## Build

```bash
npm install
npm run build          # production: tsc --noEmit â†’ vite build â†’ vite content (no popup debug UI)
npm run build:dev      # development mode on both Vite steps; popup includes test fill + clear vault
npm run build:content  # rebuild only the content script
npm run watch          # vite build --watch --mode development (popup/bg; rerun build:content when content changes)
npm run typecheck      # tsc --noEmit only
```

The two-step Vite build is intentional: `vite.config.ts` bundles the popup and background as ES modules, while `vite.content.config.ts` produces a single-file IIFE (`dist/content.js`) with `inlineDynamicImports` â€” required for reliable MV3 content script injection and to ship `totp-generator` + `neverthrow` inside the content bundle.

## Loading the extension

**Firefox:** `about:debugging` â†’ Load Temporary Add-on â†’ select `dist/manifest.json`

**Chrome/Chromium:** `chrome://extensions` â†’ Developer mode â†’ Load unpacked â†’ select `dist/`

Rebuild and reload the extension after any source change.

